-- Mobile TeleSystems Buys Tascom WiFi Network for $38.3 Million
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-28T18:26:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/mobile-telesystems-buys-tascom-wifi-network-for-38-3-million.html
OAO Mobile TeleSystems,  Russia ’s
largest mobile-phone operator, acquired ZAO Tascom, a Moscow
WiFi network, for $38.3 million through a subsidiary, Moscow
City Telephone Network, also known as MGTS, according to an e-
mailed company statement.  An additional payment of $6.9 million has been delayed for
12 months, MTS said. MGTS accepted $9.7 million in Tascom’s
debt, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
